### Authenticated application pages

**Discover page** (`/discover/content/trending`) serves as the main content marketplace with tab navigation across **Dashboards, Queries, Creators (Wizards), and Teams**. Sort options include Favorites (1/7/30 days, all time), Trending (1/4/24 hours), and New. **Tag-based filtering** uses clickable pill chips (DeFi, NFT, DEX) and a blockchain filter dropdown. Advanced search supports structured syntax: `title:`, `tags:`, `author:`, `code:`, `created_after:`, and exclusion with `-tags:`.

**Library** (`/library`) functions as the personal workspace showing all user-created content. It supports **folder organization** (Free: 2 folders, Plus: 10, Premium: 50), a context switcher for personal vs. team accounts, and dedicated management for schedules and data uploads.

**Query Editor** (`/queries/new` or `/queries/{id}`) is the platform's core workspace with a **three-panel layout**: a left sidebar Data Explorer for browsing tables by chain/protocol, a center SQL editor with syntax highlighting and AI assistance, and a bottom results panel with tabs for query results and multiple visualizations. Key toolbar elements include Run/Run Selection, engine size selector (Small/Medium/Large), AI prompt button, parameter insertion (`{{param}}`), format query, explain query (GPT-4), and Try API. Settings offer fullscreen mode, syntax themes, tab size, diff view, and autocomplete toggle.

**Dashboard view** (`/{username}/{dashboard-slug}`) displays a **free-form widget grid** with drag-and-drop positioning. Widgets include chart visualizations (bar, line, area, scatter, pie), counter/KPI boxes, and Markdown text blocks supporting images/GIFs. Dashboard controls include edit mode toggle, Run All Queries refresh, parameter controls for cross-widget filtering, embed generation, screenshot capture, GitHub linking, and privacy settings. **URL slugs are immutable** once set, though display names can change.

**User profile** (`/{username}`) shows published dashboards, queries, star count reputation, and an activity heatmap (GitHub-contribution style). **Team profiles** operate under team namespaces with Admin/Editor/Viewer roles and unlimited free teammates.

**Settings** (`/settings/...`) covers subscription management, billing, credit usage, API key generation, team member management, profile editing, and query cost caps.

**Contract decoding** (`/contracts/new`) lets users submit smart contract addresses and ABIs for Dune to parse into queryable tables, with ~24-hour processing time.

**Authentication** (`/auth/register`, `/auth/login`) uses email-based signup — notably not wallet-based.

