## Visualization and dashboard system enables flexible data storytelling

Dune provides **seven core visualization types**: line charts, bar charts (stackable, horizontal/vertical), area charts (stackable), scatter charts, pie charts, counter/KPI boxes (single-value display), and formatted tables. **Mixed graphs** can combine multiple chart types in one visualization, except pie charts cannot mix with others. The visualization editor uses a tab-based configuration system: Chart Options (title, legend, stacking, data labels), Result Data (axis column selection, grouping), X-axis/Y-axis Options (scale, format, logarithmic), and Series Options (rename, recolor, reorder, per-series chart type).

The **dashboard builder** uses a gravity-based grid where widgets always try to move upward. Edit mode enables drag-and-drop widget positioning and corner-drag resizing. Text widgets render Markdown with support for headers, bullet points, bold/italic, inline images via URL, and hyperlinks — functioning as annotation and narrative elements. **Dashboard-level parameters** surface interactive filter controls (dropdowns, date pickers, text inputs) that apply across all parameterized query widgets simultaneously, with an "Apply all parameters" button.

**Sharing mechanisms** include URL sharing for all public content, iframe embeds for external websites (`<iframe src="https://dune.com/embeds/{query_id}/{viz_id}/{token}">`), CSV export (paid tiers), API endpoints generated via "Try API" button, and social sharing with visualization screenshots. Free-tier dashboards display **Dune watermarks** removed at Enterprise level.

